<author><name><![CDATA[Gaurav]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-05-06T22:35:17-07:00</updated>
<published>2014-05-06T22:35:17-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2603&amp;p=12690#p12690</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2603&amp;p=12690#p12690"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Customize Start Menu for All User]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2603&amp;p=12690#p12690"><![CDATA[
For single user, the settings are stored at this key: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\IvoSoft\ClassicStartMenu\Settings (Note the \Settings subkey). Copy the MenuItems7 string value from here.<br /><br />But for all users, the settings are stored at: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\IvoSoft\ClassicStartMenu (HKLM branch and no \Settings subkey). The MenuItems7 string value you copied above should be created here.<br /><br />Finally, exit the Start menu and start it again or log out and log in again.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue May 06, 2014 10:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
